OL,6,FHigher borrowing costs, weak growth
OL,7,Fand persistent inflation means the
OL,8,Fchancellor was on track to break one
OL,9,Fof her new fiscal rules at the first
OL,10,Ftime of asking.
OL,12,FBack in October, the OBR thought she
OL,13,Fwould succeed in balancing spending on
OL,14,Fpublic services with tax revenues in
OL,15,Ffive years' time with #9.9 billion to
OL,16,Fspare.
OL,18,FThat headroom is gone. Indeed, the OBR
OL,19,Fcalculates she's set to overspend by
OL,20,F#4 billion.
